		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Bulwer-Lytton Fiction Contest</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>The <b>Bulwer-Lytton Fiction Contest</b> (BLFC) is a <a href="/wiki/Tongue-in-cheek" title="Tongue-in-cheek">tongue-in-cheek</a> contest that takes place annually and is sponsored by the English Department of <a href="/wiki/San_Jos%C3%A9_State_University" title="San José State University">San José State University</a> in <a href="/wiki/San_Jose,_California" title="San Jose, California">San Jose, California</a>. Entrants are invited "to compose the opening sentence to the worst of all possible novels" — that is, deliberately bad. A prize of <a href="/wiki/US$" title="US$" class="mw-redirect">US$</a>250 is awarded.<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since May 2008" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup></p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
<tr>
<td>
<div id="toctitle">
<h2>Contents</h2>
