<p><small><i><a href="/wiki/Montendre" title="Montendre">Montendre, France</a></i></small></p>
</td>
<td>As the newest Lady Turnpot descended into the kitchen wrapped only in her celery-green dressing gown, her creamy bosom rising and falling like a temperamental souffle, her tart mouth pursed in distaste, the sous-chef whispered to the scullery boy, "I don't know what to make of her." <sup id="cite_ref-lyttony_1-13" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-lyttony-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>1991</td>
